alternatives.transcript: This line chart shows the stock prices of four major technology companies, Amazon, Microsoft, Apple, and Google, for each year from 2017 to 2023. We can see that the stock prices of all four companies have increased over time, but at different rates and patterns. Amazon has the highest and fastest-growing stock price among the four, reaching $4500 in 2023, more than double the second-highest company, Google. Google has the second-highest stock price among the four, surpassing Microsoft and Apple in 2019 and 2020 respectively, and reaching $2200 in 2023. Microsoft has the third-highest stock price among the four, growing steadily from $62 in 2017 to $350 in 2023, with no significant fluctuations. Apple has the lowest and most volatile stock price among the four, dropping from $293 in 2020 to $182 in 2021, and then rebounding to $200 in 2022, before falling again to $150 in 2023. This chart reveals the different performance and trends of the four technology giants in the stock market over the past seven years.
